07/08/2007
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- Kosovo police arrested four suspected weapon dealers according to media reports Monday (August 6th).
The arrests Sunday evening involved two different locations.
Three people were apprehended as they allegedly tried to sell machine guns and ammunition, while the fourth man was found carrying an AK-47 and more than 700 bullets.
This is second operation against illegal arms sales in Kosovo within a week.
Last week, police apprehended two people and found a cache of weapons near the village of Podujevo.
(Blic - 07/08/07;
Tanjug, B92 - 06/08/07)
